		"Name": "Daikyu",
		"Details": "Named for an anicent Japanese longbow and first produced in 3055, the Daikyu is armed for long-range combat. The design has a high ground speed for its weight, allowing it to dictate the range it engages the enemy at and keeps it in optimal range for its guns. The Daikyu DAI-02 is the a more dedicated brawler variant of the chassis, though it remains built on the same 350 XL engine and Endo-Steel structure as the original. The DAI-02 carries an ER PPC for ranged combat but it is truly at home up close with twin Streak SRM-6s and ER Medium Lasers. Five jump jets give it unexpected mobility while a C3 Slave computer ties it into allied targeting networks.",
		"Icon": "uixTxrIcon_daikyu"
	},
